      "content": "You speak as if life is a problem to be solved with \"gentle support,\" but you do not understand the elegance of an ending. Some stories are not meant to linger in the gutter, fading into a messy, undignified decay. They are meant to conclude with a flourish, a final, quiet stillness that preserves the tragedy as it was intended. Don't you see? There is a profound, dark harmony in letting go before the light is entirely gone. It is the only way to remain untainted by the coming years of misery.",
